<paragraph id="63F7568D2B5D26E8286DBD0CFAF3BD4D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="82713C07BDC3086E50908827BC95AB5C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.139.47872" author="Calvo, J" journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="29 - 38" refId="B7" refString="Calvo, J, Funk, VA, 2020. Two new species of Xenophyllum (Senecioneae, Compositae). PhytoKeys 139: 29 - 38, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.139.47872" title="Two new species of Xenophyllum (Senecioneae, Compositae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.139.47872" volume="139" year="2020">Calvo and Funk (2020</bibRefCitation>
: 32, fig. 2, as photo).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D4EBF29F2E6D1629A75707E129F40B52" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="DF7195E8EEBB88A0F049D0B8ADF108AA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="16DACA45C3531691AC5D8E5B24A819D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Endemic to Ecuador (
<normalizedToken id="FD5D6053073D166646099D25F13DE04C" originalValue="Bolívar">Bolivar</normalizedToken>
, Chimborazo). This species grows in exposed places and on sandy soils of the dry superparamo ecoregion, at elevations of 4100-4300 m (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E5B446DF094102210E67A7CA2AF392C0" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Distribution map of Xenophyllum sotarense (left hand, closed triangle), X. roseum (left hand, open circle), and X. funkianum (right hand)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.158.50848.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448889" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A7A10827E860D254CF11751343B8FBCF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The species is known from a few collections near the Chimborazo Volcano. Its distribution area partially overlaps with those of 
<taxonomicName id="3C2E325DEA1F10F6D01FD9E54B475FB7" genus="X." lsidName="X. humile" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="humile">
<emphasis id="3E6460CCA3A2F9C926BD71332BC9444B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. humile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B0B8CFF904A2900C4D25981BC4EC29E1" genus="X." lsidName="X. rigidum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis id="54EAE996DEF58DF89CB6F2D8D8726876" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. rigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. See 
<bibRefCitation id="05AED3D17E13A84886601ED2CC41717A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.139.47872" author="Calvo, J" journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="29 - 38" refId="B7" refString="Calvo, J, Funk, VA, 2020. Two new species of Xenophyllum (Senecioneae, Compositae). PhytoKeys 139: 29 - 38, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.139.47872" title="Two new species of Xenophyllum (Senecioneae, Compositae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.139.47872" volume="139" year="2020">Calvo and Funk (2020)</bibRefCitation>
for further details.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A52FA84EE48D9FA84E80E9583AAE00F9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="phenology">
<paragraph id="09CB3859682BDE1BAD092BD893656815" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F8831D5C1327142B2D2E982527385E1E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Flowering from April to July.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6C12602D572E335A052309404D1D45AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="48107F0EA38DB6FEA5D00CE7D3E11264" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3E89422E1660C73958F2CE0FD5425986" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The epithet honors the American botanist Vicki A. Funk (1947-2019), who described the genus 
<taxonomicName id="D6C048AFB3329291F9564606C4854044" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Xenophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xenophyllum" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BF131D5633200DEEE3DD1FA5D8FFE6D4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xenophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and greatly contributed to the understanding of the family 
<taxonomicName id="85578165DB66BD7220E0A7C42A5AB0AB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Xenophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Compositae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7343F9D760A5B84694F34A90DE8F312F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="F9C6B871BF0E6E42425EC821879FAF48" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9DD54D3B027425850DECB0E59B7F9356" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="2A90A8CCDF89E1062F437CA251EC51F4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Xenophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xenophyllum funkianum" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="funkianum">
<emphasis id="337A6809C34FE0DE8CBC5873DE7B35B9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xenophyllum funkianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by its creeping rhizome-like stems 20-35 cm long, the straight linear leaves extending into a sheath-like base that bears arachnoid trichomes, the dark-burgundy sessile involucres with 13 to 14 involucral bracts, the 12 to 13 ray florets with white corollas somewhat purplish beneath, and by having white-villous achenes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8435E3963E03A3ABF52CFB3FE32C7553" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The morphologically closest species is 
<taxonomicName id="B150E9F6D1C895B3EE204D8E5A4FA406" genus="X." lsidName="X. rigidum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis id="2EA0C684263F73CED9986E1ED0EAAF85" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. rigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, they can be differentiated by the leaf lamina size (5.3-7.8 
<normalizedToken id="E6A7DE4DE3196A4DBE4D1EEEC9FE5341" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8-0.9 mm in 
<taxonomicName id="74EA39E43D2BEA7E39C1EFFDF6F3702B" genus="X." lsidName="X. funkianum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="funkianum">
<emphasis id="B8FD4FF07F65873F34F6C5CFA376891F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. funkianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 12.6-13.5 
<normalizedToken id="A5EFE27E4097B08279CC9CD31324662E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.3-2.4 mm in 
<taxonomicName id="D2F30B9F064B6966C1FE5A8F62696EE8" genus="X." lsidName="X. rigidum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis id="7A567B2500C08BDD08CE55356A1A2421" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. rigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), involucre size (9-11 
<normalizedToken id="367554C8428D8E6B9D1911314698A12D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-7 mm in 
<taxonomicName id="1142BFCCEA49E67984E8EE47E6E839DF" genus="X." lsidName="X. funkianum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="funkianum">
<emphasis id="3B1041881B159B471AAADB4E8A0694E5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. funkianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 11.5-12.8 
<normalizedToken id="82185D78B97136A77A2C5FDA76A070EB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7.2-11.3 mm in 
<taxonomicName id="2603DCD9CB4E20EF72B3B767EAF2BC49" genus="X." lsidName="X. rigidum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis id="2CD846F2C310EC70C6E0F45CC20CFC9E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. rigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), number of disc florets (20 to 23 in 
<taxonomicName id="3A8B6E688CA809A70BA719802D98270A" genus="X." lsidName="X. funkianum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="funkianum">
<emphasis id="6D379DE2B327ECDEDA45B6B668A7BC2E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. funkianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 38 to 41 in 
<taxonomicName id="FF2661BBA7F3CE9FDF0F48774BBCF9D4" genus="X." lsidName="X. rigidum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis id="3922E8A146797EDD2CE27C8DD2F81C01" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. rigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and by the way of growing of the rhizome-like stems (distinctly horizontal in 
<taxonomicName id="4FED5F1BFB362B706B300E920E54A139" genus="X." lsidName="X. funkianum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="funkianum">
<emphasis id="518B57716CB1DCBC7D9D5AB764CCE8EA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. funkianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. rather erect in 
<taxonomicName id="AA93A04750087EC5DE365F7F01AA29C9" genus="X." lsidName="X. rigidum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis id="10F803B036E7A10A0EF7C47BC99A85F9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. rigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="F53C43D81BAE24D8382A3863D59E882A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Xenophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xenophyllum funkianum" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="funkianum">
<emphasis id="B20D280B7D8673CC84B2DC58D68AF356" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xenophyllum funkianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is, furthermore, a smaller plant and the capitula are not enclosed among the leaves as in 
<taxonomicName id="164E9DADF84396EA4DE04CDE06EBF635" genus="X." lsidName="X. rigidum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis id="4726B59E1F28DCB8828CF1D095744A1C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. rigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Another similar species is 
<taxonomicName id="DD40045856D4CFC12CEE011B5164E50C" genus="X." lsidName="X. humile" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="humile">
<emphasis id="E2E5C628587EBA6F8BEEAC35F8E12D34" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. humile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; they differ in involucre length (9-11 mm in 
<taxonomicName id="BC6F9B85EA867519609A30D36B3D0438" genus="X." lsidName="X. funkianum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="funkianum">
<emphasis id="71C26B2DB52DDEB9A49D626EB90FAF2B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. funkianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 4.6-9.3 mm in 
<taxonomicName id="D3EE9B654CB6462A97CC435F8944DDC1" genus="X." lsidName="X. humile" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="humile">
<emphasis id="C4A35A2419B34FBB326C1FC4D9F32D11" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. humile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), achene indumentum (white-villous in 
<taxonomicName id="CD5B95155A1D4F182C040CBC2C2C8745" genus="X." lsidName="X. funkianum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="funkianum">
<emphasis id="4C69F5A26649AE369FEFD5AD5A3A9E50" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. funkianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. glabrous in 
<taxonomicName id="08AE340EC8EE61710946FB97B6C9E81A" genus="X." lsidName="X. humile" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="humile">
<emphasis id="0682338032C140BC402F3A928B4BD985" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. humile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and habit (rather creeping in 
<taxonomicName id="9A0AFC8C77FC51A8771314574D54145E" genus="X." lsidName="X. funkianum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="funkianum">
<emphasis id="1A7FE007236F23EDF356D59D924A4E5D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. funkianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. forming dense mats or hummocks in 
<taxonomicName id="989586F4F6DD798E425339277DAD3D1A" genus="X." lsidName="X. humile" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="humile">
<emphasis id="A8A2BE1D57061FB10C69B781921AB46E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. humile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Moreover, 
<taxonomicName id="3E43B844C705FFCBC84F3EFF309DB556" genus="X." lsidName="X. funkianum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="funkianum">
<emphasis id="497204686D79A171F7F16045FE5C2F0F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. funkianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having the leaf lamina barely spreading from the sheath-like base (vs. leaf lamina usually spreading at nearly 90° from the sheath-like base in 
<taxonomicName id="58AC777DD5F1645A629E4FB264188C37" genus="X." lsidName="X. humile" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="humile">
<emphasis id="BE4DB781A7E25B5223B6520D97756635" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. humile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
